author: ShMaCo33
body: Great post! I found Kendu, like many others, searching for a community in which I feel like I can make a difference, both for myself and the community. I started "working" by making patches, as in Kendu Unstitched, which was my way to say thank you to the Kendu Street team for their contributions but also get the brand out there in a tangible way...a trinket to show one's Kendu spirit! My initiative continues by, what I call, shill cards, which are business cards and stickers I hand out locally that guide people to Kendu, using a QR code which links to the well-made kendu.io web page; it's like a portal to the greatest decision one could make! I believe in this community because of the many Chads & Chadettes, around the world, who share a common idea, and THE Kendu attitude!  We don't gamble. We work!

author: Hot-Raspberry2758
body: I downloaded reddit alittle over a year ago and was looking though it and came across a post for kendu. I glanced at their MC and it was at 10M(googled kendu). A month later I happened across another post from them and decided to go read their reddit page. By this time MC was alittle higher(~15) and decided to buy a small bag. As price rose I continued buying bags, up until 150M MC. After kendu dropped to 6M because of youknowwho, I got nervous(I never sold, never would), but by now, I still has hope in the community.   We started climbing back to 10M, and I saw firsthand how strong and dedicated our community really is. Without our diamond handed members, we would have surely lost it all crashing to 6M. I see and hear what our members are creating irl and I'm glad to be a part of this IRL CRYPTO MOVEMENT! I look forward to when we üöÄ and I'm able to go to irl gatherings( music festivals, ect).
